    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for CC'ing me @vjpai. \n\nI am working on somewhat a major change to our sync server and would be removing the \"threadpool\" from the sync-server. \n\nInstead, each server can have a configurable number of completion queues (which is set to the number of CPUs by default) and each completion queue will have a configurable number of polling threads (both minimum and maximum per completion queue which would be set to 1 and infinity respectively).\n\nIn your case you would then be setting the number of completion queues via server builder .\n\nI am planning to have this change merged in the next one month or so..\n"
  },
